Head. Ommatidia 1+1. PAO narrow with distinct constriction, almost as long as width of base of Ant. I, and with inner denticles. 5–6 guard setae present behind PAO (
Fig. 1
). Maxillary palp bifurcated, maxillary outer lobe with 4 sublobal hairs. Labral setal formula 4/5, 5, 4. Labium with 4+4 basomedian setae. Ventral side of head with 4+4 setae along linea ventralis (ventral groove) (
Fig. 2
). Ant. I, II, III respectively with 2, 3, 1 basal microsensilla, and 2, 1, 5 sensilla (
Fig. 3
).

Body chaetotaxy. Macroseta (Mac) obviously longer than ordinary seta. Sensillum (s) thinner­walled, shorter and more slender than common setae. Microsensillum (ms) thickwalled and shorter than common seta and sensillum. Formula of body macrosetae as 1, 1/ 3, 3, 3, 4 per half tergum, longest on last 3 abdominal segments 3.7–4.6 times length of mucro. Sensillar and microsensillar formula respectively as 3, 3/2, 2, 2, 3, 5 (s) and 1, 0/1, 0, 0, 0 (ms). Medial accessory p­row sensillum (accp) situated between Mac 1 and Mac 2, in front of p­row on Abd. I–III and in p­row on Abd. IV. Corner sensillum just in front of p­row on each segment of Th. II–Abd. IV. Outermost anterolateral sensilla on Th. II absent. Abd. V with 5+5 sensilla in normal positions. (
Fig. 4
) Axial setae (common setae along median line on each side) of Th. II–Abd. III: 9–10, 6(7), 4, 4, 4. Th. III with 28–32 setae in p­row. Thorax without ventral setae.

Appendages. Tibiotarsus with many additional setae besides three rings, each with seven cheate (A1–A7, B1–B7, C1–C7). Tenent hairs absent. Unguis and unguiculus toothless. Upper and lower subcoxa with 3 (2) and 8 (6) (leg II), 4–6 and 8 (7) (leg III) setae (
Figs. 5 & 6
), respectively. Ventral tube with 3+3 latero­distal and 5–6 posterior setae (
Fig. 8
). Retinaculum with 4+4 teeth on rami and 1 (2 found in one specimen) large setae on ventral side of corpus (
Fig. 9
). Anterior part of furcal subcoxa with 5 (6–7) +5 (6–7), posterior part with 4+4 setae (
Fig. 10
). Manubrium anteriorly with 2+2 setae, apical ones large and basal ones small; posteriorly with 4+4 latero­basal, 3+3 central, 2+2 distal, 1+1 apical. Dens crenulated, anteriorly with 7, posteriorly with 2 basal and 1 medial setae (
Figs. 11 & 12
). Mucro with 2 teeth. Ratio of manubrium: dens: mucro as 3.9–4.9: 3.6–4.4: 1.

Male genital plate. With 13 outer and 2+2 inner setae. 4 anterior and 3+3 posterior setae present in peripheral area (
Fig. 13
).
